root_cause:
In the code:

```cpp
for (i = 1; i < td->td_samplesperpixel; i++) {
    fprintf(fd, " %5" PRIu16, td->td_transferfunction[i][l]);
}
```

There is a vulnerability due to the improper size of the `td_transferfunction` variable. It is defined as `td->td_samplesperpixel - td->td_extrasamples` instead of `td_samplesperpixel`, which results in an out-of-bounds array access vulnerability.
